description: Come and pick up a self-guided tour of Woolwich, learn more about the Woolwich Heritage Action Zone and 'Meet the Collection', a chance to see some of the collection from the Borough's Museum and Archive collection.

events.name: Meet and Greet
events.notes: The event takes place in the library.

factsheet.heading: Woolwich Heritage Action Zone and Meet the Collection
paragraphs: Woolwich is one of only a few London boroughs to have been awarded funding from Historic England to bring a new lease of life to Woolwich. The fund is being delivered by Historic England and will unlock the potential of high streets, fueling economic, social and cultural recovery and breathe new life into town centers for future generations. This will be a chance to learn a little more about the heritage program that will support this project, share your stories and explore the area using one of our free self-guided walking tours that will take you around this fascinating town. In addition our NLHF project, Meet the Collection, will showcase items from the borough's fascinating and unique museum and archive collection.

name: Woolwich Heritage Action Zone
